# bwimport

R package that uses C++ to import data from bigwig files either local or remote

## Installation
```r
# install.packages("remotes")
remotes::install_github("slaish/bwimport")

### Example
library(bwimport)
bw_URL = "http://genome-ftp.mbg.au.dk/public/THJ/seqNdisplayR/examples/tracks/HeLa_3pseq/siGFP_noPAP_in_batch1_plus.bw"

chrom = "chr12"
chrom_start = 6531808
chrom_end = 6541078

vals = bw_import(bw_URL, chrom, chrom_start, chrom_end) # [1] 9503.29


On Windows (R 4.5.x + Rtools 4.5), open "Rtools bash (ucrt64)" and run:
  pacman -S --needed --noconfirm mingw-w64-ucrt-x86_64-curl mingw-w64-ucrt-x86_64-zlib
 
Then install:
  remotes::install_github("slaish/bwimport")      # or your meta-package
